Residents of Ivory Coast Town Tiebissou Report Gun Fire and Explosions

-- B y   P a u l i n e   B a x
-- 
2011-03-30T08:44:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/residents-of-ivory-coast-town-tiebissou-report-gun-fire-and-explosions.html
Fighting between rebels and forces
loyal to  Ivory Coast ’s President Laurent Gbagbo has begun in the
central town of Tiebissou, Michael Kouakou, a resident. said in
an interview today.  “The shooting started at 2 a.m. this morning,” he said.
“We haven’t slept or left the house. It is still continuing, we
are hearing machine guns and sometimes explosions.  Tiebissou lies on the border of a former buffer zone
between the rebel held north and the government-controlled
south. It lies on the road between Bouake, the rebel capital in
the north of the country, and Yamoussoukro, Ivory Coast’s
capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pauline Bax in Johannesburg at 
